    "strategy_description": "10-step heterologous pathway from L-phenylalanine to glabridin was added to iMM904 (11 reactions including exchange). Baseline theoretical max was 0.667 mmol/gDW/h. Overexpression of ZWF1 (G6PDH2r) and GND2 (GND) at min_flux=1.5 maintained near-theoretical-max production (0.666 mmol/gDW/h) at 10% biomass constraint. PDC quadruple knockout (PDC1/5/6 + ARO10) disabled ethanol fermentation and Ehrlich pathway but reduced max product flux to 0.452 due to redox imbalance; recommended as optional for fed-batch conditions. Production envelope shows classic growth-production tradeoff with full production at low growth rates."
  }
